.\" man page for stethoscope
.TH STETHOSCOPE 1 "July 8, 2026" "stethoscope 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
stethoscope \- vital signs for your Mac
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B stethoscope
.I scope
.RI [ command ]
.RI [ args ]
.RI [ --json ]
.RI [ --once ]
.RI [ --duration
.IR N ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B stethoscope
is a machine\-health observability tool for macOS: structured probes over the
OS's native introspection surfaces, presented for humans (CLI/TUI) and
consumable by agents. Each subsystem is a
.IR scope :
a namespace of commands backed by a reusable data layer. Every number a human
sees and every field an agent reads comes from the same function, so a probe
can be rendered as a table or emitted as JSON without divergence.
.PP
Everything it touches ships with macOS
.RB ( libproc ,
.BR fs_usage ,
.BR lsof ,
.BR vm_stat ,
.BR ioreg ,
.BR pmset ,
.BR diskutil ,
system Python 3). There are no third\-party dependencies;
.B smartctl
is used opportunistically by the
.B smart
scope if it happens to be installed.
.SH SCOPES
.TP
.B disk
Per\-process disk I/O visibility.
.RS
.TP
.B top
Who is doing disk I/O now (default). Ranks processes by read/write per second.
.TP
.B inspect \fIpid\fR
Why \(em a live \fBfs_usage\fR syscall trace for one pid (needs root).
.TP
.B holds \fIpid\fR
What on\-disk files a process holds open.
.TP
.B busy \fIvolume\fR
Which pids pin a volume/device open ("why won't it eject").
.TP
.B tui
Full\-screen interactive view (run with \fBsudo -E\fR).
.RE
.TP
.B cpu
Per\-process CPU utilization and wakeups.
.RS
.TP
.B top
Rank processes by CPU% (default). Utilization is machine\-relative; a process
saturating two cores reads ~200%.
.TP
.B wakeups
Rank by idle+interrupt wakeups per second \(em battery\- and scheduler\-hostile
processes even at low CPU%.
.RE
.TP
.B memory
Per\-process footprint and leak watching.
.RS
.TP
.B top
Rank by memory footprint (default); header shows system pressure.
.TP
.B watch \fIpid\fR
Sample one process's footprint over time; report the slope (MB/min) and flag a
leak candidate.
.RE
.TP
.B battery
Power drain and battery health.
.RS
.TP
.B health
Charge, cycle count, capacity vs design, condition (default).
.TP
.B top
Rank processes by an energy\-impact score (CPU% + weighted wakeups).
.TP
.B drainers
Cumulative energy impact since you last unplugged.
.RE
.TP
.B smart
.RI [ disk ]
Drive health, wear, and life expectancy. SMART status plus \(em when
\fBsmartctl\fR is installed \(em wear percentage, TBW, power\-on hours, spare
capacity and pre\-failure warnings. Exits non\-zero if any drive is critical.
.TP
.B checkup
A one\-shot full\-body exam: samples every scope once and prints a health
verdict with findings and the drill\-down command to confirm each.
.TP
.B mcp
Run a Model Context Protocol server over stdio, exposing the scopes as agent
tools. Usually launched by an MCP client, not by hand.
.SH AGENT / SCRIPTING FLAGS
.TP
.B --json
Emit one structured JSON document per sample instead of the human table
(newline\-delimited for streams). Shapes are documented in SCHEMA.md.
.TP
.B --once
Take a single sample and exit (sampling commands).
.TP
.B --duration \fIN\fR
Sample for \fIN\fR seconds, then exit.
.TP
.B --interval \fIN\fR
Seconds between samples (default 1).
.TP
.B --limit \fIN\fR
Rows to show (default 20).
.SH EXIT CODES
.TP
.B 0
Ran fine; nothing notable / clean.
.TP
.B 1
Ran fine and the probe found the thing (\fBbusy\fR: holders exist; \fBmemory
watch\fR: leak candidate; \fBsmart\fR/\fBcheckup\fR: critical).
.TP
.B 2
Bad invocation.
.TP
.B 3
Needs root / permission denied.
.SH A NOTE ON SUDO
The kernel shows a process's accounting only to root or its owner. Without
sudo you see your own processes but not other users' or system daemons \(em and
daemons are frequently the answer. Run the sampling and holder commands under
sudo for full\-system coverage;
.B inspect
requires it. The TUI wants
.B sudo -E
so curses keeps
.BR $TERM .
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Who is hammering the disk, then why:
.B sudo stethoscope disk top
.br
.B sudo stethoscope disk inspect 12345
.TP
Why won't this drive eject:
.B sudo stethoscope disk busy "/Volumes/X9 Pro"
.TP
Is a process leaking memory:
.B stethoscope memory watch 12345
.TP
What's draining the battery since I unplugged:
.B stethoscope battery drainers
.TP
One\-shot machine health, for a script:
.B stethoscope checkup --json
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/Library/Application Support/stethoscope/battery_baseline.json
Baseline snapshot used by \fBbattery drainers\fR.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR fs_usage (1),
.BR lsof (8),
.BR vm_stat (1),
.BR pmset (1),
.BR ioreg (8),
.BR diskutil (8),
.BR smartctl (8)
.PP
The JSON output contract is documented in SCHEMA.md in the source tree.
